<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2245c</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chinese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Yung Kwai</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-31"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                    1919</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Lansing’s Note No. 82
                                of October 8, 1918,<note n="99" xml:id="d377fn99"><ref target="frus1918#pg_196"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                            Relations</hi>, 1918, p. 196</ref>.</note> on the
                                subject of the formation of an international group for the purpose
                                of rendering financial assistance to China, I have the honor to
                                enclose herewith for your information and for the information of
                                your Government copy of an identic note with accompanying enclosure
                                on the above mentioned subject, which I have today handed to the
                                representatives of Great Britain, France and Japan.<note n="1" xml:id="d377fn1">See note to the British Chargé, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi></note></p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Breckinridge
                                Long</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>